inn1.comm: starts with a length delivery around off, Devcich defends it on the leg side with a thick inside edge
towards the leg side this time on length, tucked towards midwicket
outside the off stump now, Devcich goes on the back foot and punches to cover point
fuller outside off, he drives it just between cover and mid off for one
back of length on the off stump, Brownlie goes on the back foot and defends on the leg side
that's a bit too wide and timed beautifully through the off side for four! There was room outside off, Brownlie made a bit of room as well and caressed it between point and cover point
outside off on length and swinging away, left alone
beaten! Touch fuller outside off, it was angled in but the ball held its line to go straight as Devcich played inside the line and drove to miss it
swing and a miss again! This was fuller and wider, Devcich chased without moving his feet and could not connect again
brings it in this time, he goes back and defends it back
goes back to the line outside off, Devcich stays back and defends again
fuller just outside off, driven uppishly just past point towards third man
from back of length outside leg, he defends off the back foot on the off side
touch shorter outside leg and with the angle, Devcich waits for it and taps it with soft hands to the slip
short of length from middle and leg, Devcich wants to pull but doesn't middle it that well
swing and another miss! Angled across from the batsman outside off, bit of movement off the pitch, and Devcich drove uppishly and missed
bit too short outside off, Devcich gets room this time and cracks it for four with a back-foot cut past point to beat third man as well
on length this time outside off, pushed down the track to mid off
length delivery angled across, he leaves it alone
fullish on the pads and that's clipped away on the leg side to the midwicket boundary before Misbah cuts it. Good running to collect three there
slightly back of length outside off, defends towards the covers off the back foot
beautiful timing from Devcich off the back foot - it was a bit short and wide outside off and he stayed back to punch it between cover point and point for three
on length on the off stump, defends off the back foot
that's an appeal for caught behind as it was nearly in the block hole well outside off, Brownlie looked to tap it and the ball went to first slip. The umpires get together and say it's not out
back of length outside off, he taps it late to third man for one
too wide outside off, easily caressed between point and cover point off the back foot in the gap
back of length outside off, punched off the back foot to short cover
touch wider outside off, pushed off the back foot on the off side
on length outside the off stump, pushed to point
touch shorter outside the off stump, punched to extra cover off the back foot
angled towards the pads, clipped on the leg side between mid on and midwicket for one
full on the off stump, Brownlie gets a thick inside edge down to fine leg
further towards the pads with the angle, worked to fine leg this time
too short, maybe he was expecting that, he went on the back foot and pulled it from outside off past midwicket for a cracking four

that's the first breakthrough and a very good catch at point from Shehzad! Too wide outside off, Brownlie chased with a swish uppishly and the ball was dipping towards point but Shehzad dived to his right, almost full length, to catch it
superb delivery for a new batsman! Teasing line outside off, angling away, Williamson looked to poke but missed it as it went past him
too full outside off, driven firmly straight to short cover
short outside off, Devcich frees his arms and slaps it between cover and extra cover from the middle of the bat for three
back of length just outside off, defends off the back foot to the leg side
bit closer to off stump, worked on the leg side again off the back foot
on length just outside off, pushed on the leg side past midwicket for a single as Misbah gets a direct hit at the non-striker's end
slower delivery at 121kph from the leg side, Devcich waits for it and defends
swinging away from outside off, beats KW again! It was back of length around off, KW didn't move much and poked as the ball whizzed past the outside edge
on length on the off stump, not as much swing, and he defends this time
on middle and leg now, pushed to midwicket by KW
KW connects the outswinger and absolutely middles it this time! It was outside off and shaping away, he waited for it and punched it off the back foot off the toes through the covers for four
full on the pads and he clips it to the leg-side boundary this time for four! It was too full and KW put it away past midwicket with good timing
on length and shaping away outside off, left alone this time
rolls his fingers over this one pitched short of length on leg, tapped on the off side for one
short of length outside off, punched off the back foot to the covers
swing and miss! Slightly short of length outside off, this one landed on the seam and held its line to beat KW's back-foot punch
full and angling in, shaped in as well and thick inside edge goes does to fine leg for one
short of length outside leg, pulled late and straight to short fine leg
too short outside off now and that's a cracking four off the back foot, but thanks to a misfield at point as well
back of length outside off, pushed off the back foot to short cover
right on target on the stumps, blocked on the leg side
fuller and outside off and angling away, left alone easily
short outside off, KW pulls on the leg side, but too early and gets the toes of the bat to sends the ball short cover
bangs it in shorter outside off, and with away swing, KW looks to pull but leaves it in the end

the short ball does it, KW pulls and gets a leading edge to send it high for an easy catch for the keeper! The short balls were not stopping, KW decided to pull after leaving the previous one and got a top edge this time, Sarfraz takes a couple of steps toward slips and catches it
starts with a fullish delivery outside off, driven down the ground and a misfield at mid off gives them two
length delivery wider outside off, left alone
on the pads this time, clipped straight to midwicket by Taylor
too full outside off and Taylor drives it beautifully through the covers by reaching out for it a bit, making a small stride with his front foot
on length outside off, this one's not full and Taylor lets it go
on length on the off stump now, pushed tentatively into the covers
turning in from outside off, he comes down and defends it back

that's through and Sarfraz misses a stumping! Sharp turn from outside off, Devcich came down to drive but the ball went through the gate and just over the stumps to beat the keeper. Umpire gives it byes
waits for it and swishes to sweeper cover for one
comes down again and drives it with the turn to long on
works to deep midwicket with the turn for one
on length outside off, driven down to long off for one
length delivery on the pads, tucked to midwicket off the back foot
swings and misses! Full delivery outside off and swinging away, Taylor chases it with a drive and misses
on length on the off stump this time, he blocks it back
on length just outside off, pushes it down to mid on
short of length on the leg stump, tucked off the back foot towards square leg
short down the leg side as Devcich looks to pull and it's a wide
straying towards the pads, worked down to fine leg for one
lots of flight and it's full outside off, driven straight to short cover
sharp turn from outside off, Devcich looks to cut by making room but doesn't connect well
turns it too much down leg for a wide
turning into the pads, clipped to midwicket with the turn
full on middle, clipped to deep midwicket for an easy single
flighted on the stumps, driven down to long on for one
loud appeal for lbw from Sohail as it turned towards the pads. Devcich looked to work it on leg but was struck around the middle stump. Replays show it was going down leg
on length outside the off stump, pushed into the covers
fuller outside the off stump, driven down easily to long off for one

edged for the keeper, Wahab has removed the settled batsman! The length delivery nipped in from outside off, Devcich chased it without any footwork, played the wrong line as it came in and got an inside edge for the keeper. That's drinks now
length delivery outside off, shapes away a touch, Latham defends it towards point
stays in the crease and dabs the back of length delivery towards point
some space outside off, Latham gets off the mark with a glide to third man
tossed up outside off, the batsman slices it towards point
tossed up wide outside off, the batsman drags it to deep backward square leg with a sweep
pushed through on the stumps, Taylor punches it back to Sohail
short and outside off, Taylor waits and cuts it to deep point
another well-played sweep, Latham picks it up from wide outside off and clatters it to deep square leg
waits on the back foot and cuts it firmly to deep point
length delivery on off, 143 kph, the batsman comes forward and defends it down the pitch

drifts on to the pads and pays the price for it, Taylor gets a faint tickle on it as he clips it to the fine-leg boundary. Umar Gul dives and gets a hand to it, but can't prevent it from reaching the ropes
back of length and angling away, the batsman leaves it alone
he comes forward and steers the fuller delivery to Shahzad at point
he wanted to punch this through covers but gets a thick inside edge towards midwicket
digs it in short as there is a deep square leg in place, the batsman ducks under it
gets a bit of a top edge as he sweeps this from outside off, played to deep square leg
comes forward and defends the fuller delivery down the pitch
lots of flight on this one, easily driven to wide long-on
much slower this time, Latham has only one shot at the moment - sweep. Manages to paddle it down to fine leg
quicker delivery on off, Taylor waits and punches it to deep cover for a single
flatter and shorter this time, so Latham chooses to stay upright, but still drags it to deep square leg with a pull
presents a lot of width with this 141 kph delivery, Latham has to stretch out as he punches it to deep point
back of length on off, Taylor is in no hurry, punches it to cover
he leans forward before letting this angled delivery pass
pounds it halfway on the pitch but Taylor ducks to get out of the way
back of length on the pads, clipped down to fine leg with ease
length delivery outside off, the batsman comes forward and defends
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman comes forward and drives it to long off
another sweep, drags it from outside off to deep backward square leg
nice gentle pace from Sohail, the batsman chops it to backward point
slower and tossed up, the batsman defends it to cover
pushed through on the stumps, the batsman defends it down the pitch
tossed up on the stumps, eased to long off for a single
tossed up on the middle stump line, Taylor pushes it towards point
nice drift from Lala, flighted on towards the pads, Taylor pushes it back down the pitch
quicker delivery sliding in towards middle and leg, more defence from Taylor
slower this time, the batsman uses more defence
much quicker than what Taylor anticipated.. bounces extra too. Hit the bat high up as he defends
he looks for the gap at backward point but can't beat the fielder
another sweep shot from Latham but this was almost fatal. He gets a bottom edge and it's not far from the stumps
more sweeping here, Latham gets this off the middle to deep backward square leg
surprise surprise.. no sweep now. He punches it to deep cover off the back foot
flatter and on the stumps, the batsman defends it to the leg side
tossed up on the off, Taylor is not fussed about scoring runs, pushes it back to the bowler
tossed up down the leg side, the batsman looks for the sweep but misses.. but this is well down the leg side
similar lines from the bowler, and Taylor looks for the big sweep again. But it hits the pad and rolls fine on the leg side
pushed through on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to cover
oh how precise is that! The backward point dives to his left, the short third-man dives to his right.. neither can cut off Taylor's cut shot
on the pads this time, he comes forward and defends it down the ptich
quicker one on the middle stump, defended down the pitch again
slower but still on the middle stump, defended down the pitch
drifting on to the pads, but Taylor chooses to defend it, pushed to the leg side
sweep shot attempted for the millionth time! This time he gets a little top edge over the keeper's right shoulder
looks to drive this tossed up delivery inside out but finds the man at cover
pushed through on the pads, Taylor nudges it to square leg for a single
goes deep in the crease and whips the tossed up delivery to square leg
sweeps again, but finds the man at short fine leg
looks to come down the pitch but Sohail tosses it well wide outside off, Latham has to shelf is plan of going downtown.. he punches it to midwicket
pushed through on off, Taylor pushes it in the gap at cover for a quick single
tossed up on off, Latham comes forward and punches it to long on
what precise cutting this! He takes it off from off stump and gets enough on it to beat the short third-man fielder. It's fine on the off side and down to the boundary

it's over, it's all over! Taylor wanted to take a single with a dab to cover but he didn't realise how close it was to the fielder. Younis comes in quickly and flicks it underarm to the keeper who takes the bails off in a nanosecond. Latham dived full length but it was of no avail. He has to go
tossed up on off, the batsman pushes it back at the bowler
he pushes forward to defend but gets an inside edge to the leg side
short and wide outside off, slow too, it sits up for Taylor and he whacks it powerfully through to deep extra cover for a couple.. Wahab dives to prevent the boundary
wrong line from Sohail. This is on the pads and Taylor sweeps it powerfully through deep backward square leg
tossed up on the stumps, Taylor defends to off
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman cuts it to backward point
lots of loop here, driven down to long off for a single
flatter and on the stumps, the batsman defends it to the leg side
looks to cut this one from off stump but this just bounces a touch extra and beats the edge
slider on the middle and leg line, the batsman defends it down the pitch
loopy delivery on the stumps, the batsman defends it to cover
quicker one outside off, Taylor looks to cut but finds the man at backward point
full and on the pads, Taylor punches it to long on for a single
tossed up on off, Neesham drives it to cover
he goes back and punches it to long on
quicker one, comes in sharply from outside off, Neesham is surprised and gets a thick inside edge
dabs it to short third man, Taylor calls in for a quick single and dives in to complete it in time
shorter and flatter outside off, slapped through to deep point
uses his feet and drives the tossed up delivery to long on
almost punches it into the hands of the bowler.. Played that a touch too early

that's a very very good shout for lbw from round the wicket! They are going for a review after Aleem Dar said no. Neesham didn't have a clue. This was tossed up but Neesham stayed back, then pushed tamely outside the line.. This one turned in and hit the pads in front of the middle. That is hitting leg stump. It looked out the moment his missed it. Bad one for Dar, good one for Lala
tossed up on the stumps, driven straight to mid-on
punches this in the air through the right of cover fielder, picks up a single to long off
poor delivery! This is well down the leg side and Sarfraz does well to cover it. Afridi apologises immediately
tossed up outside off, the batsman comes forward and slices it to deep point
quicker delivery on off, Ronchi defends it off the back foot
quicker one on the stumps, the batsman pushes it from the crease towards mid-on
tossed up on off, the batsman pushes it to cover
loses his direction, this is well down the leg side
tossed up on off, slower as well, the batsman can only dab it to backward point
lots of air on this one and Taylor was looking for the gap at deep extra cover, but is not able to beat the man at cover
short and slower, Taylor misses out as he gets a bit of bottom edge playing the cut.. picks up a single to cover point
nice and loopy outside off, Ronchi watches it go through to the keeper
nicely tossed up again, the batsman defends
tossed up on the stumps, Taylor pushes it to long on
full and flighted on the middle, the batsman drives it back to Lala
much slower this time, Ronchi has to wait before defending it to cover
loopier this time, Ronchi comes forward and defends it down the pitch
goes for the big drive as soon as he sees width, but this one zips away sharply to beat the bat.
some turn again, the batsman pushes it to the right of the point fielder for a quick single
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman dabs it to midwicket for a single
looks to drive the length ball on the up but get hit high on the bat.. Asks for a change of gloves immediately
comes forward and punches the fuller delivery down to mid-off
back of length and coming in a touch, the batsman defends it down the pitch
no room on this one, Taylor punches it back to Gul
gets up on his toes and punches this to deep cover for a single
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman pushes it down to long off
slower and outside off, Ronchi waits before punching it through to deep cover
down the leg side, Taylor nudges it through square leg for a quick couple of singles
quicker delivery, but this is down the leg side. The batsman misses his clip shot
he pushes forward and steers the tossed up delivery to deep cover
shorter and outside off, the batsman punches it to extra cover
back of length outside off, the batsman squeezes it out through point for a single to bring up his half-century
just short of length and the batsman swivels to whack it through to deep midwicket boundary
crash! This is short and wide and Ronchi slaps it through point, powerfully enough to beat anyone in the vicinity
back of length and on off stump, the batsman punches it back to the bowler
short of length outside off, the batsman rides the bounce and crashes it to deep point, just a single though
waits for the slower delivery and dabs it to cover for a single
fullish on the pads driven back to the bowler
length delivery angled across from round the wicket, punched to sweeper cover off the back foot
touch fuller outside off, taps it late to short third man
short and flat outside off, pushed down to deepish mid off
flat and quick on the stumps, cuts it late to backward point
flighted and full, that's in Ronchi's zone and he's launched it straight down the ground over the bowler's head for a four. Mid off was in and he took advantage of that
angled in from back of length towards the batsman, taps it on the leg side
outside off this time, pushed off the back foot into the covers
offcutter from outside off, Taylor looked to push it down but looked like something distracted him and just got bat on that
bit straighter this time and Taylor defends it back again
too short and Taylor pulls to his favourite area - deep midwicket for two
tight line and length just outside off, Taylor defends it back. Just two from the over
starts from outside the leg stump, the ball deflects down to short fine leg for a leg bye
slightly full outside off, Taylor drives it into the covers
on length outside the off stump, he pushes it towards point with soft hands for a quick single
on length on middle and off, pushed straight to cover point
fuller on the off stump, pushed on the off side for another quick single
slightly wider outside off, Taylor looks to slice it and misses. He looks disappointed. Just three from this over
well outside off and swings it away further from the batsman for a wide
that's too short and well outside off, Ronchi stays back to smack it with a pull between mid on and midwicket for a four. There's nobody in the deep there
angles it in to reduce the room for Ronchi, he cuts it to point
swing and miss! It was slight short of length outside off with the angle, but the ball seamed away after pitching, making Ronchi miss it

oh he's given it away and that's a great catch from Younis running back! It was a short ball again, Ronchi pulled half-heartedly and the leading edge went high on the leg side. Younis ran towards the boundary from midwicket and caught it with a dive near the 30-yard circle with this arms stretched outwards

edged and four just past the keeper! There's no slip - Irfan came back to over the wicket, drew an outside edge from Taylor with this ball outside off and some swing, Taylor poked and only managed it past Sarfraz who dived but it was out of his reach
wider outside off, Taylor wants to crash it on the off side but manages a bottom edge near the pitch
slightly full outside off, pushed into the covers
fuller on the off stump, pushed on the off side again without much footwork
back of length outside off, pushed down to mid off this time
he gets room and finds the gap nicely between point and cover point with a push after waiting for the ball to come to him to get off the mark
around off stump, pushed past cover point for one
bouncer is angled in and it goes over Vettori as he ducks under it
drives the fullish ball uppishly down to mid off
back of length outside off, thick outside edge goes down to third man
nearly a yorker down the leg side as Vettori shuffles across and that's called a wide
lbw appeal as it strikes Vettori on the pads, it was angled in sharply but was going down leg
attempted yorker is a full toss on the leg side, tucked wide of mid on for one
another edge off Taylor's bat and it flies down to third man for one. Was pitched outside off, Taylor swung his bat and didn't middle again. Was well wide of the slip fielder
shuffles across and clips the ball to deep square leg for one
he sweeps the length ball from outside off towards deep square leg and Harris runs to his left and dives to save two
tucked towards midwicket with soft hands for one
slices the length ball outside off to short third man
flipper towards the off stump, pushed on the off side in the gap for a quick single
on middle and leg, and Vettori reverse sweeps it behind square on the off side
fullish outside off, driven with the turn towards sweeper cover
slow delivery at 121kph on the pads, clipped to deep midwicket for one
short ball outside off, pulled nicely to deep midwicket for two
angled in from length outside off, Vettori looked to drive but the bat turned in his hands and the ball rolled down to mid on
another attempted yorker is a full toss on the pads and Vettori works it with the angle, using the pace to beet fine leg for four runs
short this time around off, pulled from the middle of the bat - one bounce to deep midwicket
angled across the off stump, punched off the back foot to deep point
on length around off, pushed towards point tentatively
right on target on the stumps, Taylor blocks it back
slightly more flight on the middle stump, pushed down to the bowler
flighted outside off, he swishes it with the turn towards deep backward point for two
flatter and quicker just outside off, Taylor wants to slice again but misses this time
flighted on middle and leg, pushed down to long on for one
moves across a long way to the off side to pull the back of length delivery but takes it around the left thigh as he fails to connect
he connects this time, it's gone all the way and where he wants it - midwicket region! Short ball, he was ready for it and smacked it over deep midwicket to send it all the way
outside off this time and pushed a bit wide of point for one
nearly in the block hole outside off, pushed into the covers
shuffles across towards off, flicks it on the leg side with the wrists for one
too full and wide and Taylor gets enough room to free his arms, drives it through the covers for a four
he comes down the track and slogs it in the air down to long on
slightly outside off and he slices it towards backward point for a quick single, that's NZ's 200
turning in from outside off, Vettori attempts to reverse sweep it but misses and Sarfraz whips the bails off but he's safe inside
worked with the turn to the leg side for one
fullish outside off and he paddles it towards short fine leg where Irfan dives and deflects the ball towards the boundary behind the keeper. They have time for three
appeal for lbw as Vettori tries the reverse sweep again, the ball deflects off the pad on off and they sneak in a leg bye. Probably hit him outside the line. And that's the 50 partnership
Vettori is not going to be defensive here - makes room and hammers the short ball down the ground over mid on's head for a one-bounce four
oh, what a shot! Made room again, stayed in the crease, got a full delivery again and drove it inside out over the covers for four more. There was nobody in the deep there
makes too much room this time and lets the ball go outside off. Wahab bowled it outside his reach

bang on target, hits the stumps! Wahab replies with a superb ball on the stumps and Vettori misses it this time. He shuffled too far across for the full delivery that was swinging in towards middle, looked to work it on leg but missed and was bowled the way he was in the 2nd T20
on length outside off and he taps it late to third man for an easy single
another swing and a miss from Taylor! Length delivery outside off, goes for a big drive but the ball beats the outside edge
back of length outside off, pushed off the back foot towards cover point
shuffles across a bit, tucks the ball off the pads to deep midwicket in the gap for two
fantastic delivery - outside off on length, McCullum shuffled across a bit again and the angle and bounce missed the outside edge as he poked
touch wider outside off, pushed to backward point this time
short ball angled across this time, McCullum tries the upper cut but the ball swings away and that's called a wide
length delivery towards middle and leg, worked off the pads to deep square leg
that's too wide outside off, full as well, and Taylor swings his arms to drive it over the covers for four. Moves into the 90s
low full toss outside off, pushes it on the off side for one
short ball just outside off, McCullum doesn't get room and defends it close to himself
beaten by pace! Slow and low full toss outside off at 109kph, McCullum looked to smash it on leg but missed
high full toss outside off, swishes it to deep point for one
appeal for caught behind as Taylor looks to glance the ball down leg, umpire calls it an over so that would have taken the pad
slightly slower at 127kph outside off, worked to third man to give Taylor the strike
short and wide, he upper-cuts it to the third-man region in the gap and Harris cuts it off to restrict it to two
back of length on the leg side now, pulled to deep backward square leg for one
bouncer towards McCullum, he pivots on the back foot and hooks it to fine leg for one
back of length outside off, slapped to sweeper cover for one
shuffles across early and drives the ball from outside off to sweeper cover, and keeps strike
shuffles across again and works the full toss from middle stump to the leg side for one
full delivery outside off, driven firmly in the air down to long after two bounces and they take two

nasty short ball hits him on the jaw, but after some glove, he sneaks a run for his hundred but looks in pain too. Took his eyes off the ball as the ball rose towards his face, the ball hit his right thumb and then his left cheek. It was a no ball too
full on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket for one
slower ball at 119kph towards the leg side, gets some bat as he pulls it behind square on leg
full and slightly wide outside off, driven firmly through the covers, wide of sweeper cover, and they run fast for the third
full toss to end the innings, Taylor is not going to let that one go, slaps it over the covers from outside off and beats sweeper cover easily for four. Finishes on 105*

inn2.comm: length delivery outside the off stump with hint of outswing, left alone
touch wider and shaping it away again, Hafeez shoulders arms
fuller and closer to off, pushed down to mid off this time
nice shape again for the length delivery outside off, left again
straighter one on length outside off, he lets it go to the keeper
fuller towards the stumps, driven on the leg side now
well outside off and it's left alone for the keeper
back of length just outside off, he defends off the back foot
full with outswing outside off, he drives and gets a thick edge down to third man for one
swings this one in from outside off, Hafeez leaves it alone
144.5kph, walks towards the delivery outside off, it shaped in and he played the wrong line completely as the ball went past the inside edge
past the outside edge this time, beaten again! He didn't move much this time, drove outside off and the ball shaped away to just miss the outside edge, superb bowling
bit of outswing from well outside off, he leaves it alone
closer to off stump, this one shaped in, Shehzad put his front foot forward and left again
short of length outside off, punched off the back foot to cover point
drives a bit outside the line as the ball nipped in and thick inside edge goes to midwicket where the fielder dives to save a few runs
holds its line a bit outside off, Shehzad pushes tentatively on off
touch fuller outside off, pushed back to the bowler and maiden again from Mills
that's a drop technically, but an amazing effort from Latham at midwicket! Hafeez flicked the full delivery off the pads in the air, Latham jumped but only got a hand to it and they take two
shapes it away from outside off, given a wide
142.4kph, nice shape for the length delivery outside off, Hafeez leans forward and leaves the ball. Good bounce as well
drives the length ball again, thick outside edge is racing to third man boundary where Vettori dives and keeps it to two. Hardly any footwork there, Hafeez looking not so confident
fuller on the pads, Hafeez flicks it from the middle but straight to midwicket
back of length outside off, cuts it late to steer it to third man
fullish on off and that's been driven down the ground to just beat a diving mid off for four! Bit too full and Shehzad didn't drive it firmly, just timed it beautifully
shuffles across towards off to pull the back of length ball, gets an inside edge onto his body
fullish outside off, driven nicely past short cover towards wide mid off for one
length delivery around off, pushed back to the bowler
charges down the track, drives the fullish delivery and guides it to third man for one

superb delivery to get rid of Hafeez, who was not looking good today! It had the scrambled seam on length outside off, Hafeez moved towards the ball and left a gap between bat and ball which the ball sneaked through, deflected off the pad and hit the stumps
straighter outside off, he stays back and taps it on off
147.6 kph, angled in towards the stumps, steered to the leg side
147kph, on length outside off again, pushed down to mid off
142kph, beaten by pace! He pulls the short ball from outside off that came in slightly but the ball hits the sticker of the bat to fall on the leg side
goes on the back foot and defends the ball outside off from length
fuller outside off and it's driven a bit wide of mid off
147kph, length ball coming in from outside off, he leans forward and blocks
edged and falls short of point! That one squared him up as he looked to defend, the ball got an outside edge and flew towards point
that's a confident drive, that goes all the way, beautiful drive! Shehzad leaned into it a bit, full delivery and caressed it through the covers
down leg from Mills this time and four more! It was angled towards the pads, Shehzad glanced it past short fine leg for four
straighter delivery around off, pushed down past the bowler for one
back of length outside off, he stays back and defends
shuffles across a bit and flicks the ball to mid on from outside off
short ball outside off, Shehzad pulls it for four with the aerial route. It wasn't that short, he didn't get the middle of the bat but only had to clear the infield and did so easily
152kph, doesn't move much and defends the ball down towards mid on
152.4kph, short ball outside off, looks to crash it between point and cover point but doesn't time it well because that was quick!
150.5kph, much fuller outside off and driven firmly but straight to short cover. He is hardly moving his feet though
full again and wider outside off, driven past short cover this time for one
145kph, short delivery outside off, he slaps it down towards cover point, doesn't time it well
what a shot! Comes down the track and drives that handsomely inside out over the covers with a high elbow for a cracking four! That should give him some confidence
length delivery outside off, left alone this time
back of length outside off now, taps it late on the off side for one
shorter outside off, he wants to steer it off the back foot but misses the timing
fuller and angled in, pushed down to mid on this time
draws the outside edge, squared him up a bit as well and he's off the mark as it goes down to third man
143.4kph, back of length outside off, pushed down to mid off
straighter one this time from Milne, pushed down to mid on now
wide outside off on length, swishes at it, straight to point
angles in the bouncer at 148kph, Shafiq ducks under it
fullish outside off again, steers it in the air past point for one
back of length outside off, Shehzad sways out of the line a bit and taps it to point
fullish outside off, driven down to long off for one
flighted wider outside off, steered to sweeper cover for one
touch short of length on off, he makes room and cuts it to sweeper cover
flighted and fuller on off, he leans forward and defends it
flighted around off again, he defends slightly on the wrong line now and gets inside edge on leg
straighter on the stumps, blocks it on the leg side
back of length outside off, he guides it towards point and Devcich dives to his left to stop that
checks his drive a little bit for this not-so-short delivery and it nearly carried to Taylor at short cover
back of length outside off now, cuts it to deep point
that's a simple catch for Devcich at point, Shafiq's scratchy innings is over! Short of good length outside off, he cut it straight to Devcich for a waist-high catch
almost a mix up on his first ball, he leaned forward for the length delivery to defend it on off and both batsmen took start and both went back
straighter delivery on off, he defends it back to the bowler
bit of flight outside off, he presses forward and defends
leans forward again and blocks the delivery outside off
steers the length delivery to cover point now
draws a bit of outside edge with the turn from length outside off

Vettori has struck, Shehzad is gone! That was the arm ball sliding in towards the stumps from outside off, Shehzad went way back in the crease and covered his stumps, the ball came in struck him right in front of the stumps past the bat, finger went up immediately. Pakistan decide not to review it
towards middle and leg, clipped off the pads to midwicket for one and he's off the mark
back of length from middle and leg, tucked off the back foot to the leg side for one
strays down the leg side for a wide now
length delivery well outside off, Younis takes a big stride towards the ball and blocks
bit of extra bounce for the shorter delivery, goes off the shoulder of the bat to leg as Younis defends again
fullish outside off and that's driven handsomely to sweeper cover, Younis off the mark
wide down the leg side past Sohail's pads this time
full delivery angled across outside off, driven to sweeper cover
full and angled in towards off, punched down to mid on
length delivery around middle, he blocks it back
drifts down the leg side, deflects off the pad down leg
flighted and full outside off, driven into the covers with a forward lean
that's a risky single, Younis gets there on time with a dive. Drove it just wide of cover, the fielder dived to his right and threw it quickly to the bowler but Younis made it
tucks the fullish delivery to midwicket
just short of lenth and pushed back, McCullum dives to stop it
fullish outside off, Younis defends it back
a bit towards middle stump, tucked to the leg side with a forward lean for one
length delivery outside off, he goes back in the crease and pushes it back
flighted on length outside off, there's turn and thick inside edge goes to the leg side
fuller on off, pushed straight to short midwicket
wider outside off, he waits for it in the crease an cuts it late to short third man, that's Pakistan's 50 and drinks
punches the flatter delivery back to the bowler
slower this time, the batsman pushes it to cover
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman flicks it through midwicket
lots of flight on this time and Younis wanted to flick it, but ends up pushing it down the pitch
flatter on the stumps, the batsman punches it down the ground to long on
flatter on the stumps, Haris pushes it to midwicket
tossed up delivery on the stumps, the batsman comes forward and defends

oh another one! Younis has swept this straight to deep backward square leg. It was a late decision on Younis' part. He was upright and went down very quickly, possibly that was the reason he didn't get the control on it. Hits it hard, hits it flat .. straight to the fielder
length delivery, he dabs it to square leg to get off strike
slower and loopy from Vettori, Misbah leans forward and defends
goes back and pushes this one through to deep cover for a single
he stays back and defends the flatter delivery to the off side
he leans forward and pushes the flighted delivery to long off
much slower from Nathan.. Sohail comes forward to defend
lots of loop this time, the batsman nudges it through square leg for a single
he stays back and punches the flatter delivery to cover
fuller and flighted, Misbah pushes it down the pitch but the bowler dives to his left to cut if off
stays back and whips the flatter delivery towards midwicket where Williamson cuts it off with a dive
stays in the crease and punches the length delivery to midwicket
fuller this time, pushes it straight back to the bowler
much slower this time, the batsman nudges it to midwicket
flatter and on the pads, the batsman whips it to deep midwicket for a single
tossed up on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
much slower.. much much slower from Vettori.. and Misbah almost plays on. The inside edge rolls past the stumps
he is staying calm, defends this one to midwicket
punches this one down the ground to long on
again, slower from Nathan, Misbah dabs it to square leg for a quick single
on the pads, the batsman whips it straight to short fine leg
waits on the back foot and punches the flatter delivery to long off
he gets a leading edge as he goes back to the quicker one.. Picks up a single to point whereas he was aiming for square leg
tossed up and slower on off, the batsman chops it to cover point
he uses his feet to drive this flighted delivery, but finds the man at cover with precision
shuffles on the crease to clip this quicker delivery to deep square leg
tossed up outside off, the batsman pushes it to midwicket
pushes it a little more firmly, but again finds the man at midwicket
this one comes in sharply from outside off, Sohail does well to chop it in front of square for a quick single
tossed up on off, Sohail goes back and works it away to deep midwicket with a wristy clip
fuller on the stumps, he pushes it back to the bowler
he has has enough! Sees the fuller delivery and throws the kitchen sink at it.. Although get it more of the toe there. Just drops short of the boundary at cow corner.. Milne was hovering close by too
cuts it through backward point for a single
tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler
comes down the pitch and looks to whip it to the leg side, but this one is cut off by the midwicket fielder
tossed up outside off, the batsman drives it to deep cover
they are getting a move on! Haris comes down the pitch, gets some width as well to swing his arms and whacks it straight down the ground
full and flighted, pushed to midwicket
flatter and quicker, he looks to cut but is beaten by the length there
still can't find the gap, tucks it straight to midwicket
quicker delivery, that is chopped towards deep point
but this one is spinning down the leg side.. No chance for the keeper
tossed up on off and middle, the batsman nudges it to square leg with the turn
appeal for lbw but that one had a big inside edge. Only the bowler showed any interest
goes back to one that stays low, punches it straight to midwicket
pushes this one past the diving bowler for a quick single to mid-on
on the pads, this is easily nudges away to deep square leg for a single
he comes down the pitch and pushes the fuller delivery down to long on
he comes forward to a length ball and defends it to point

oh my Vettori! What a stunner that is! And we thought he had fitness issues! Misbah wanted to go over the infield but gets a toe-end to his attempted loft.. But this was still going away from Vettori at mid-on.. He runs backwards and stretches his left-arm out to pluck out this one from nowhere. Excellent grab
back of length on the stumps, the batsman gets an inside edge to the leg side
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman dabs it to wide mid-on to get off the mark
length delivery outside off, the batsman defends it towards point
length delivery on the stumps, whipped through midwicket for a quick single
beautifully timed! Haris brings out the lofted drive from nowhere. He comes forward and just chips it over the infield.. Inside out and over extra cover
on the pads, the batsman works it away to square leg for a single
slower and on the stumps, easily pushed to deep cover for a single
lots of flight, the batsman flicks it to deep midwicket. The strike is being rotated nicely now
flatter and quicker on off, the batsman gets a bit cramped for room, pushes it down the ptich
pushed through on the stumps, defended down the pitch
length delivery on the stumps, solidly defended to cover
on the pads, the batsman works it away to deep midwicket for a single
superbly timed! A mere push but that has enough on it to beat mid-on and make mid-off scamper in its chase
he whips this through wide mid-on now to pick up a couple to the deep
he goes down early to play the sweep, but this is a bouncer and it sails over his head. How confident he is of these sweep shots? Amazing
back of length, dabbed in front of point for a quick single
he stretches forward to sweep it powerfully to deep midwicket
he comes down the pitch and punches the flighted delivery to long on
skip and a whack! He uses his feet early and punches it straight past the non-striker. Could have been dangerous has the flying Nath intercepted it
more positivity now.. Haris moves out of the crease and caresses this to wide long off
how easily is this done! He comes down the pitch and plays a straight drive over the bowler's head.. no chance for anyone
goes deep in the crease and bunts the flatter delivery to long on
135 kph, no problem. Sarfraz will sweep anything. He takes it from well down the crease and smashes it to deep square leg boundary. Stupendous
forces the bowler to bowl outside off, then crunches it behind point easily
effort ball from Neesham! Sir Faraz was looking to cut it through to third man but this flies past the outside edge
a repeat of everything from the last ball, but this time Sir Faraz gets bat to it, cuts it beautifully to the third-man boundary.. It was played late, and fine
back of length on the stumps, he nudges it to square leg and calls back for a quick couple. Superb running
short ball, Sarfraz ducks under it calmly
flatter on off, the batsman punches it down to long off
is that the end of the challenge! Sir Faraz wanted to whack it over wide long-on.. Just didn't get enough of it. The fielder was standing right at the edge of the boundary and Milne gobbles it up.
flatter delivery on the stumps, the batsman punches it to long on for a single
flatter on the stumps, the batsman whips it to deep square leg for a single
fuller on the stumps, the batsman tickles it straight to square leg
flatter delivery, he punches it down the pitch and a collision between Nathan and Boom Boom means the bowler is not able to stop it
back of length on the pads, the batsman whips it behind square on the leg side for a single
back of length on the stumps, pushed to mid-on with soft hands
fuller outside off, Haris stretches forward to ease it to deep cover
bowls a slower yorker at 112 kph, Lala spots it and digs it out with ease
shorter delivery on the stumps, Afridi looks to pull but doesn't get hold of it, played to midwicket
short of length delivery on the stumps, Afridi pull but bottom edges it through square leg
slower delivery on the pads, Afridi pushes it back down the pitch
shuffles at the crease but then defends this tossed up delivery to midwicket
waits in the crease and tickles it down to short fine leg
comes down the pitch and punches the fuller delivery down to long-on
he can do better. Gets his front leg out of the way and smashes this one over extra cover
fuller on off, he calmly pushes this to cover
gives him the charge but the bowler digs it short.. It's called a wide as this sails over the batsman.. A little harsh from the umpire
fuller and outside off, the batsman waits and opens the face to run it down to third man
he comes forward to push this length delivery to cover, but it flies off the face to third-man
back of length on off, Haris tucks it to square leg for a quick single
that has smacked him on the grille.. Afridi went for the pull and got a deflection from his bat on to his helmet. All good. Neesham checks on the batsman. Afridi gives him a facebook like
fulller delivery on the stumps, the batsman whips it easily to deep midwicket
slower bouncer, but this one is too high. Sails way over
back of length on the stumps, the batsman chops it to point
length delivery outside off at 146 kph, the batsman defends it towards point
slower delivery wide outside off, the batsman dabs it through point for a single
angles it in at 147.5 kph, Afridi is hurried a bit, defends it down the pitch
now a slower ball, at Nelson kph, the batsman chops it to cover
he is keeping things tight here. Fires this one at 147 kph and Lala can only defend it to midwicket
now a short one outside off, Afridi is not taking any chances, ducks under it. Time to go for a quick drink
length delivery on the stumps, calmly pushes to wide mid-on for a single
he walks across to the off side, whips the slower delivery to midwicket calmly
back of length outside off, the batsman dabs it straight to cover point
short of length on the pads, whipped away to deep square leg.
he is doing a Taylor here! Afridi waits for the back of length delivery and cuts it with surgical precision through the gap between backward point and short third-man
slower delivery on the stumps, Afridi pushes it with soft hands to mid-on for a single
gets the outside edge! But who's going to stop it? No one. That has reached the boundary before anyone had a chance to blink
slower one outside off, Afridi has spotted it early, he crunches it to deep point for a single
quick length delivery, 147 kph, Haris Sohail is still calm enough to defend the length delivery to cover
looks for the yorker, but this is a low full toss, punched past the bowler for a single to mid-off
fuller delivery on the pads, calmly tickled to short fine leg. He rubs his thighs as this one skimmed off them at 147 kph
fuller and aimed on the off stump at 149 kph, Haris dabs it towards mid-on for a quick single
fuller delivery outside off, Haris pushes it straight to cover
he waits on the back foot and defends the length delivery to backward point
length delivery outside off, he punches it through cover for a single
he goes down on his knee early and paddles it fine on the leg side. Had he missed that one, it was hitting leg stump but he does it very nicely and in a controlled manner
fuller on off, he whips it straight to square leg
shuffles across and dabs it (dabs it!!!) for a single to the off side. Smart cricket this by Lala
length delivery on the stumps, he comes forward and defends it to off
mean delivery aimed at the body, Afridi however arches back and plays it nicely to third man
he chops it on to third-man for a single
back of length outside off, calmly guided away to third-man. He is not the same Afridi we know but he is the one Pakistan need right now
fuller on the stumps, Sohail wanted to hit it towards midwicket but it came in too quick at 150 kph, he ends up punching it to mid-on
oh what a gap! Sohail reaches his maiden half-century with a neat clip off his hips.. Perfectly placed between the keeper and the man at short fine. Superb effort this by Sohail
he shuffles across and whips this fuller delivery from outside off down to fine leg
neatly timed off the front-foot! The man at mid-off is at the edge of the circle and they pick up a single easily
slower delivery and the real Afridi makes an appearance. He charges down the pitch and looks for the big slog but misses it completely
stays in the crease and runs it down to short third-man for a single
rolls his fingers on this fuller delivery, Sohail pushes it down the pitch back to the bowler
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to midwicket for a quick single
flatter and quicker on the pads, Sohail clips it to deep square leg
flatter and shorter outside off, but Afridi knows where the gap is. He whacks it all along the ground and in the gap at deep midwicket.
much slower this time, the batsman waits for it and pushes it with soft hands to cover for a single
punches it firmly towards wide mid-on but Williamson from midwicket intercepts with a dive
on the pads, tucked away to the right of short fine leg for a single
back of length outside off, the batsman defends it down the pitch
he sees width and slashes his bat at that, slicing it over point for a couple to the deep
that is quick! The batsman wanted to pull but is surprised by how quickly it reaches him.. misses it
bowls a smart slower delivery at 115 kph, Sohail defends it down the pitch
back to the normal pace, this one hurries the batsman as he defends it to off
he watches the length ball and decides to pull early, gets enough on it to beat mid-on.. Useful boundary
bowled much slower this time, Afridi punches it to long off with ease
quicker one on the stumps, Sohail tucks it to square leg for a quick single
nice bit of loop from Vettori, Afridi is in some other zone today, pushes it along the ground to deep midwicket
quicker delivery on off, pushed back to the bowler
goes deep in the crease and punches it to deep extra cover for a single
flatter delivery, Sohail calmly turns the strike over with a push to long on
slower delivery, the batsman defends it to point easily
another slower delivery outside off, Sohail punches it to deep cover for a single
he is almost beaten by the slower delivery but manages to cut it late past the keeper for a single
back of length delivery outside off, the batsman defends it to point
this is almost an offspinner, comes really slow off the surface, the batsman ends up pushing it back to the bowler
slower delivery outside off, the batsman comes down the pitch and pushes it to deep extra cover
uses his feet and pushes the flighted delivery to long off
looks to flick this quicker one but misses, gets hit on the pads
goes down on the knee early and gets the perfect length for a sweep. He also goes over the man at backward square leg, placed it perfectly
fuller outside off, he throws the sledgehammer now, hammering it down to long off
wanted to create room but the bowler bowls quicker, the batsman keeps it out in time
fuller delivery on the stumps, punched to long on for a single
superbly hit by Sohail! The mid-off was up so Sohail comes down the pitch and whacks it over the infield nicely
short one now, Sohail is still not hurried.. ducks under it easily
stays upright and punches the back of length delivery to deep cover
slower delivery on the pads, Afridi pushes it with soft hands to deep midwicket
short ball from round the stumps, Sohail is in no hurry at all, gets out of the way
attempts to bowl the back-of-the-hand slower ball but loses the direction, this is well wide outside off
fuller on off, nicely driven to mid-off who is standing at the edge, easy single there
makes room by moving outside leg and punches the length ball straight down the ground, the fielder at mid-off cuts it off

oh this could have gone anywhere! Afridi wanted to clip this short of length delivery to the leg side but got a leading edge straight back towards the bowler.. just drops short of him .. The batsmen steal a single too
moves to the leg side again and drags the short ball to midwicket for a single
fuller on off, he brings his fifty not with a six but with a calm push to deep midwicket for two. He applauds his partner.. The dressing room is up to applaud the innings too
slower delivery outside off, Afridi wanted to smash it through point but is beaten
the Afridi is in town! The length doesn't matter.. Afridi just goes with the big shot and although it looks like he hasn't got enough, it actually just eludes the long-on fielder..
slower delivery wide outside off, goes over the wide marker.. the umpire calls in favour of the batsman
another slower delivery, this is sliced to deep backward point for a couple
short delivery outside off, Sohail gets out of the way too early.. Realises later he could have just steered it to third man
comes down the pitch and dabs the short delivery to cover for a quick single. A throw comes in at Afrid's end but Williamson misses. Afridi is not happy with that call
short outside off and this has been roundhouse kicked through square leg. Slapped over the fielder at square leg

direct hit and this could be tight! Afridi hits it straight to Taylor at cover and takes off immediately. There was no single in there. Once Taylor hit, it was over for him. He gets a standing ovation for a superb 61
short delivery outside off, Sohail ramps it to third-man for a single
back of length on the pads, clipped to short fine leg for a single
he gets off strike with a push to long-on.. Sohail trusts Riaz and asks him to come back for the second as the fielder is a bit deep
poor ball from Mills, this is on the pads and all Wahab has to do is to get some bat on it.. That he does, with the fine leg up, there is no one there to stop it
quicker delivery outside off, past the outside edge
nicely crashes it to third man and calls for a second as it's Vettori down there. The throw comes in at the striker's end.. Could be a run-out..It's a tough one.. His dive has saved him
looks to swing down the ground but misses it completely.. Mills keeps appealing for a caught behind but no one else shows interest
short delivery outside off, the batsman ramps it to third man for an easy single
slower delivery on the pads, Riaz dabs it to square leg for a quick single to level the scores
short ball, Sohail finishes it with a boundary over fine-leg. Fantastic knock from Sohail and he deservingly gets to hit the winning runs
